-- Ciel of Mauritius Gains Most in 17 Months After Bid for Parent
-- B y   K a m l e s h   B h u c k o r y
-- 2012-03-07T10:23:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-07/ciel-of-mauritius-gains-most-in-17-months-after-bid-for-parent.html
Ciel Investment Ltd. (CIEL) , a Mauritian
company with interests in leisure and property, rose the most in
almost 17 months.  The stock advanced 3.9 percent, its biggest daily gain
since October 2010, to 2.70 rupees at the close in Port Louis,
the capital.  Ciel Investment is an associate company of  Deep River
Investment Ltd. (DRIL) , which said yesterday it has received an  offer 
from a “prospective bidder.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kamlesh Bhuckory in Port Louis at 
 kbhuckory@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net  